<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<!-- SECTION 2: CONVERSATION BREAKDOWN                 -->
<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<div id="sec2" class="cfe-section">
    <div class="cfe-section-header">
        <span class="badge-num">2</span> Conversation Breakdown — Guftagoo Ka Tafsili Jaiza
    </div>
    <p class="tw-text-sm tw-text-slate-600 tw-mb-4">Yeh un sawalon aur muddo ka khulasa hai jo commission system ke hawale se discuss hue:</p>

    <div class="cfe-step">
        <div class="cfe-step-num">A</div>
        <div class="cfe-step-body">
            <p><strong>Masla: Courier ke liye commission kab banti hai?</strong><br>
            Jab courier koi parcel deliver karta hai, to us delivery ka data billing server par record hota hai. Month ke akhir mein (21 se 20 tak), HR system us data ko utha kar commission calculate karta hai. Yeh ek automated process hai.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="cfe-step">
        <div class="cfe-step-num">B</div>
        <div class="cfe-step-body">
            <p><strong>Masla: Employee ka city mein hona zaroori kyun hai?</strong><br>
            Commission sirf un employees ki banti hai jo us city mein officially assign hain. Agar employee ka <code>hr_employeeroutecode</code> mein koi record nahi, ya uska location register nahi, to us ka commission miss ho jata hai. Isiliye location setup teen jagah hona zaroori hai — Server 7 (MIS), Server 6 (Billing), aur Server 10 (Main).</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="cfe-step">
        <div class="cfe-step-num">C</div>
        <div class="cfe-step-body">
            <p><strong>Masla: Route Code aur Employee Number alag kyun hai?</strong><br>
            Billing system mein courier ko uske <strong>Route Code</strong> se pehchana jata hai (maslan "3028"). Lekin HR system mein har employee ka apna <strong>Employee Number</strong> hota hai (maslan "LHE0001234567890"). Dono ko connect karta hai <code>hr_employeeroutecode</code> table jahan <code>RouteCode = '3028'</code> aur <code>Emp_No = 'LHE0001234567890'</code> saath record hota hai.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="cfe-step">
        <div class="cfe-step-num">D</div>
        <div class="cfe-step-body">
            <p><strong>Masla: City ID mismatch ka problem</strong><br>
            Billing server par Karachi ka <code>Station_id = '00592'</code> hota hai. Lekin HR server par Karachi ka City Code = <code>'001'</code> hai. Yeh directly match nahi karte. Join karna parta hai: <code>hr_city.station_id = '00592'</code> aur phir <code>hr_city.Code = '001'</code> milta hai. Agar yeh join theek na ho, to saara commission data ghum ho jata hai.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="cfe-step">
        <div class="cfe-step-num">E</div>
        <div class="cfe-step-body">
            <p><strong>Masla: COD bonus aur deduction kab hota hai?</strong><br>
            Agar courier ka COD collection record theek hai to use bonus milta hai. Lekin agar usne late payment ki ya koi irregularity hui, to deduction lagta hai. Yeh <code>hr_codcommission</code> table mein record hota hai.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="cfe-step">
        <div class="cfe-step-num">F</div>
        <div class="cfe-step-body">
            <p><strong>Masla: Attendance ka commission se connection?</strong><br>
            Commission calculate karte waqt employee ki attendance bhi dekhi jati hai. Jo din employee present tha, us hisab se commission prorate hoti hai. Formula: <strong>Total Days - Sundays - Absences + Adjustments</strong>. Agar employee bohat zyada absent raha, to commission kam hoti hai.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="cfe-step">
        <div class="cfe-step-num">G</div>
        <div class="cfe-step-body">
            <p><strong>Masla: Ek employee ke do route codes ho sakte hain?</strong><br>
            Haan, ek employee ke paas do route codes ho sakte hain (maslan ek local route aur ek cross-city route). Dono ke liye alag alag commission records ban sakte hain. Yeh <code>hr_employeeroutecode</code> mein ek se zyada rows se pata chalta hai.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="cfe-step">
        <div class="cfe-step-num">H</div>
        <div class="cfe-step-body">
            <p><strong>Masla: Akele employee ki commission reprocess karna?</strong><br>
            Agar kisi ek employee ki commission galat bani ya koi data miss hua, to sirf us employee ki commission dobara process ki ja sakti hai bina poori city ki commission dobara chalave. Yeh feature new MVC system mein available hai.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

